    <h3 itemprop="headline">Iran is accelerating cyber activity that appears meant to influence the US election, Microsoft says</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      NEW YORK (AP) — Iran is accelerating online activity that appears intended to influence the U.S. election, in one case targeting a presidential campaign with an email phishing attack, Microsoft said Friday.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/10/iran-is-accelerating-cyber-activity-that-appears-meant-to-influence-the-us-election-microsoft-says/"  >(ALI SWENSON, Associated Press, KRON4)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div></div><div class="column text"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Tue, 13 Aug 2024 20:25:48 +0000">
