           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Google rolls out Pixel 9 phones earlier than usual as AI race with Apple heats up</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. (AP) — Google on Tuesday unveiled its next generation of Pixel phones, providing the maker of Android software a head start on the next iPhone in the race to bring more artificial-intelligence services to devices that have become people’s constant companions.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/13/google-rolls-out-pixel-9-phones-earlier-than-usual-as-ai-race-with-apple-heats-up/"  >(MICHAEL LIEDTKE, Associated Press, Fox 5)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Tue, 13 Aug 2024 12:01:36 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Tue, 13 Aug 2024 12:01:36 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Sophie Austin, Associated Press, KPRC 2">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/08/13/california-gov-gavin-newsom-nudges-school-districts-to-restrict-student-cellphone-use.webp" alt="California Gov. Gavin Newsom nudges school districts to restrict student cellphone use"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">California Gov. Gavin Newsom nudges school districts to restrict student cellphone use</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      California Gov. Gavin Newsom is sending letters to school districts, urging them to restrict smartphone use on campuses.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/13/california-gov-gavin-newsom-nudges-school-districts-to-restrict-student-cellphone-use/"  >(Sophie Austin, Associated Press, KPRC 2)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Fri, 09 Aug 2024 19:26:00 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Fri, 09 Aug 2024 19:26:00 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="THOMAS ADAMSON and MEGAN JANETSKY, Associated Press, KREX 5">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/08/09/olympians-are-turning-to-onlyfans-to-fund-dreams-amid-as-they-decry-a-broken-finance-system.webp" alt="Olympians are turning to OnlyFans to fund dreams as they face a 'broken' finance system"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Olympians are turning to OnlyFans to fund dreams as they face a 'broken' finance system</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      PARIS (AP) — Dire financial straits are leading droves of Olympic athletes to sell images of their bodies to subscribers on OnlyFans — known for sexually explicit content — to sustain their dreams of gold at the Games.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/09/olympians-are-turning-to-onlyfans-to-fund-dreams-amid-as-they-decry-a-broken-finance-system/"  >(THOMAS ADAMSON and MEGAN JANETSKY, Associated Press, KREX 5)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div></div><div class="column hcwi"><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Sat, 10 Aug 2024 16:17:25 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Sat, 10 Aug 2024 16:17:25 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="RAPHAEL LEICESTER, Associated Press, PIX 11">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/08/10/paris-olympics-embrace-accessibility-technology-for-visually-impaired-fans.webp" alt="Paris Olympics embrace accessibility technology for visually impaired fans"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Paris Olympics embrace accessibility technology for visually impaired fans</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      PARIS (AP) — As Paris shines under the global spotlight of the Olympic Games, technological innovations are enabling people with visual impairments to take it in. Each Olympic venue is a mosaic of singular stories, from the athletes to the spectators.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/10/paris-olympics-embrace-accessibility-technology-for-visually-impaired-fans/"  >(RAPHAEL LEICESTER, Associated Press, PIX 11)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Sat, 10 Aug 2024 18:13:53 +0000">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Sat, 10 Aug 2024 18:13:53 +0000">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Yash Roy, The Hill">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/08/10/susan-wojcicki-former-youtube-ceo-dead-at-56.webp" alt="Susan Wojcicki, former YouTube CEO, dead at 56"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">Susan Wojcicki, former YouTube CEO, dead at 56</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      Former YouTube CEO Susan Wojcicki, one of the most prominent women in tech, has died at the age of 56 after a two-year fight with cancer, according to a statement from her husband.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/10/susan-wojcicki-former-youtube-ceo-dead-at-56/"  >(Yash Roy, The Hill)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2024-08-12T13:14:41">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2024-08-12T13:14:41">
  <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">
    <meta itemprop="name" content="Associated Press, Fast Company">
  </span>
  <div class="card-content">
    <div class="image" role="presentation">
      <img src="/static9/tech/2024/08/12/how-ftc-will-make-easier-for-you-click-unsubscribe.webp" alt="How the FTC will make it easier for you to click &#8216;unsubscribe&#8217;"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">How the FTC will make it easier for you to click &#8216;unsubscribe&#8217;</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      In the name of consumer protection, a slew of U.S. federal agencies are working to make it easier for Americans to click the unsubscribe button for unwanted memberships and recurring payment services.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/tech/2024/08/12/how-ftc-will-make-easier-for-you-click-unsubscribe/"  >(Associated Press, Fast Company)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div></div></div></fieldset><fieldset><legend><h2>
