      <img src="/static9/sports/2024/08/10/us-mens-basketball-team-beats-france-98-87-for-fifth-straight-gold-medal-at-paris-olympics.webp" alt="US men's basketball beats France 98-87 for fifth straight gold medal at Paris Olympics"
           itemprop="image" width="400" height="225"
           referrerpolicy="no-referrer" loading="lazy">
    </div>
    <h3 itemprop="headline">US men's basketball beats France 98-87 for fifth straight gold medal at Paris Olympics</h3>
    <p itemprop="text">
      PARIS (AP) — Stephen Curry was thinking about this two years ago, after winning his fourth NBA title. The only thing left for him to win was Olympic gold. And in the ultimate moment, he made sure that medal would be his. The U.S.
      <a itemprop="url" href="/sports/2024/08/10/us-mens-basketball-team-beats-france-98-87-for-fifth-straight-gold-medal-at-paris-olympics/"  >(The Associated Press, WFLA, NBC)</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/NewsArticle" class="card">
  <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="Tue, 13 Aug 2024 08:43:24 -0400">
  <meta itemprop="dateModified" content="Tue, 13 Aug 2024 08:43:24 -0400">
